    <description>The Korea Pathfinder Lunar Orbiter (KPLO), also known as Danuri, is South Korea's first robotic lunar probe designed to conduct lunar observations from an altitude of approximately 100 km. Managed by the Korea Aerospace Research Institute (KARI), the project involves collaboration with universities, research institutes, and NASA for various aspects such as payloads and deep space communication. The spacecraft is equipped with propulsion systems, tracking systems, communications antennas, solar arrays, and six scientific instruments. The KPLO aims to map the lunar environment, demonstrate technologies for planetary exploration, foster international cooperation, and establish a deep-space communication network, serving as a key component of the Korea Lunar Exploration Program (KLEP).</description>
